80.8	Snowboarding	Snowboarding	Snowboarding is a sport that involves descending a slope that is covered with snow on a snowboard attached to a rider's feet using a special boot set onto a mounted binding. The development of snowboarding was inspired by skateboarding, sledding, surfing and skiing. It was developed in the U.S.A. in the 1960s to 1970s and became a Winter Olympic Sport in 1998.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Powder_turn.jpg/250px-Powder_turn.jpg
